Key Match Events: The Washington Wizards won their 6th game of the season, beating the Chicago Bulls 125-107.
Bub Carrington led the team in minutes played with 31, going 4 for 5 from the field, including 3 for 3 from three-point range, and finished with a +/- rating of 12.
Justin Champagnie scored 15 points and grabbed two rebounds, going 6 for 8 from the field and 2 for 3 from three-point range.
